            <strong>Image 1:</strong> During the first treatment, hair must be visible at the skin's surface.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            <strong>Image 2:</strong> When we direct the laser beam at the hair, the heat energy is absorbed by the melanin, which heats up the rest of the hair shaft as well.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
            <strong>Image 3:</strong> The heat either weakens or completely destroys the hair follicle. As a result, the follicle separates from the hair shaft.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            <strong>Image 4:</strong> The hair falls out, and since the follicle is no longer present, hair cannot regrow in that area.
          </p>
        </div>

